The error "ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'src'" occurs because Python does not automatically recognize src as a module when running the script directly.

âœ… Solution: Use PYTHONPATH or Run from Project Root
Option 1: Set PYTHONPATH (Recommended)
Run this command before executing the script:

Windows (Command Prompt / PowerShell):

sh
Copy
Edit
set PYTHONPATH=%CD%
python src/main.py
Linux/macOS (Terminal):

sh
Copy
Edit
export PYTHONPATH=$(pwd)
python src/main.py